    PL: M-28 audit-blocker fixes — clean expander + cap + integration tests
    
    Codex code audit verdict was NOT_READY with 1 blocker + 2 mediums.
    All three addressed:
    
    BLOCKER #1 — "ZERO agency-specific strings" violated by docstring
    examples. Fixed: rewrote regulatory_expander.py docstring and
    comments to be fully generic (no FDA/EMA/agency names, no
    jurisdictional terms, no clinical-domain leaks). Added
    TestNoHardCodedHostsInModule guard test that scans the module text
    at CI time for banned substrings; if a future edit reintroduces
    agency names the test fails.
    
    MEDIUM #2 — no query-count cap on anchor queries. Fixed: introduced
    PG_SWEEP_MAX_REGULATORY_ANCHORS env var (default 10). Expander
    truncates anchor list to the cap. Env overrides allowed; invalid
    env falls back to default; zero or negative disables the cap. 5
    new TestAnchorCountCap tests cover default, override, zero,
    invalid, and negative.
    
    MEDIUM #3 — test coverage holes (YAML integration, guard test).
    Fixed: added 5 TestYamlTemplateIntegration tests that load the
    edited clinical/policy/due_diligence templates via load_scope_
    template, verify the regulatory_anchors field is exposed, and
    run the expander end-to-end. A test for the tech template (zero
    anchors by design) verifies the no-anchor case.
    
    Tests: 688 → 699 (+11 follow-up tests). All pass.
    
    Next: re-dispatch Codex for re-audit. No V18 sweep until verdict
    is READY.
    
